1. Podman run - Create and start a new container from an image. This command runs an instance of the 'nginx' image in the background with the containername "mycontainer".
      podman run [optional] <image>
For example - podman run -d --name mycontainer nginx.

2. Podman ps - lists the running contsiner. This command lists all the running containers along with their details such as container ID, image used, status, ports etc.
For example - podman ps

3. Podman images - Lists all the available images. This command displays a list of available container images on the system, including their repository, tags and image ID.
For example - podman images

4. Podman pull - Download an container registry. Yhis command fetches the latest version of 'ubuntu' image from the default container registry.
For example - podman pull ubuntu

5. Podman stop - Stop running container. This command stops the 'mycontainer' container, gracefully shutting it down. 
For example - podman stop mycontainer

6. Podman rm - Remove a stopped container. This command removes the 'mycontainer' container, deleting it from the sytem.
For example - podman rm <container>

